WEBVTT

00:01.130 --> 00:03.439
- I THINK THIS ONE'S SHAPING UP
TO BE A REAL STINKER.

00:03.480 --> 00:04.708
WANT TO HELP OUT?

00:04.760 --> 00:06.580
- PRINCIPAL TAYLOR ASKED ME
TO COME HERE AND SPICE IT UP.

00:06.620 --> 00:07.609
- HE WHAT?

00:07.660 --> 00:09.548
IF YOU DON'T LIKE HOW
I'M DIRECTING THE PLAY,

00:09.590 --> 00:11.797
YOU SPICE IT UP
HOWEVER YOU LIKE.

00:11.830 --> 00:13.582
- ALEX.
- ADAM BRAVERMAN.

00:13.630 --> 00:14.767
- NICE TO MEET YOU,
MR. BRAVERMAN.

00:14.800 --> 00:15.869
- I WAS WONDERING

00:15.910 --> 00:17.593
IF YOU'D LIKE TO COME OVER
SOME NIGHT FOR DINNER.

00:17.630 --> 00:18.665
- I'D ACTUALLY LOVE THAT.

00:18.700 --> 00:21.282
I'M IN A.A.

00:21.330 --> 00:23.844
- IT'S BEST IF YOU DON'T SEE
ALEX ANYMORE.

00:23.880 --> 00:26.189
GORDON, I KNOW THAT THINGS
HAVE BEEN ROUGH,

00:26.230 --> 00:28.607
AND YOU'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT SELLING THE COMPANY--

00:28.640 --> 00:30.028
- IT'S SOLD.

00:33.610 --> 00:36.124
- OH. HONEY.
- HI.

00:36.170 --> 00:38.058
- YOU'RE AMAZING.
- THANK YOU.

00:38.100 --> 00:39.021
- SOMETIMES I FORGET
TO TELL YOU

00:39.070 --> 00:41.345
HOW AMAZING YOU ARE,
BUT YOU'RE AMAZING.

00:41.380 --> 00:42.608
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

00:42.660 --> 00:44.685
- [muttering]
HONEY, THOSE ARE FOR HADDIE.

00:44.730 --> 00:45.697
THOSE ARE NOT FOR YOU.

00:45.730 --> 00:47.721
- OH, THEY'RE GUILT PANCAKES,
AREN'T THEY?

00:47.770 --> 00:49.385
- NO, THEY'RE NOT
GUILT PANCAKES.

00:49.420 --> 00:51.069
- YOU'RE RESORTING TO BRIBERY.
- I AM NOT.

00:51.120 --> 00:53.076
- I THOUGHT THAT THEY
WERE COMFORT PANCAKES FOR ME,

00:53.120 --> 00:54.519
SO I'D FEEL LESS ANXIOUS
ON MY FIRST DAY OF WORK

00:54.570 --> 00:55.639
WITH THE NEW BOSS.

00:55.670 --> 00:57.535
- YES. AND YOU CAN HAVE SOME...
- OKAY, THANK YOU.

00:57.570 --> 00:58.798
- FROM THE REJECT PILE.
- YEAH, I KNOW.

00:58.850 --> 01:01.603
YEAH, I KNOW THE REJECT PILE.
- I DIDN'T SLEEP LAST NIGHT.

01:01.640 --> 01:03.881
I FEEL REALLY BADLY
ABOUT THE WAY THINGS HAPPENED.

01:03.920 --> 01:06.263
AND H HATE BREAKING
HER HEART.

01:06.300 --> 01:07.881
I JUST--I DO, HONEY.
- KRISTINA, LISTEN TO ME.

01:07.920 --> 01:10.263
HE'S 19.
HE HAS HIS OWN APARTMENT.

01:10.310 --> 01:12.619
- I KNOW, BUT...
- HE'S A RECOVERING ALCOHOLIC.

01:12.650 --> 01:14.470
I LIKE THE KID. I DO.
BUT WE'RE DOING THE RIGHT THING.

01:14.520 --> 01:15.509
- I KNOW WE ARE.
GOOD MORNING.

01:15.550 --> 01:16.585
- HEY, SWEETIE.
- HI.

01:16.620 --> 01:18.508
- HI.
I MADE YOU SOME PANCAKES,

01:18.560 --> 01:20.278
CHOCOLATE CHIP--YOUR FAVORITE,
FAVORITE, FAVORITE.

01:20.320 --> 01:22.140
- I DIDN'T ASK FOR ANY PANCAKES.
- I KNOW.

01:22.180 --> 01:23.283
BUT I WANTED TO MAKE THESE
FOR YOU.

01:23.320 --> 01:25.242
THEY'RE CHOCOLATE CHIP.
- WELL, IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

01:25.290 --> 01:26.518
IT'S NOT GONNA FIX
EVERYTHING.

01:26.560 --> 01:28.118
I DON'T CARE.
- SHE SAVED YOU THE GOOD ONES.

01:28.150 --> 01:29.799
I HAD THE BURNED ONES.
- DON'T TREAT ME LIKE A BABY.

01:29.840 --> 01:32.115
I'M JUST GONNA HAVE COFFEE.

01:32.160 --> 01:34.299
- FINE. I GOT YOU
SOME HAZELNUT CREAMER

01:34.330 --> 01:35.638
THAT YOU ARE GONNA LOVE.

01:35.680 --> 01:39.298
- WELL, I JUST WANT IT BLACK.

01:39.340 --> 01:40.409
WELL, IT'S TRUE.

01:40.440 --> 01:43.614
- THERE YOU GO.

01:43.650 --> 01:45.197
GREAT.

01:45.240 --> 01:48.755
- NOW CAN I HAVE ONE OF THOSE?
- YEAH. EAT IT.

01:48.790 --> 01:50.678
[Amber singing]

01:50.730 --> 01:52.721
- HEY, AMBER, DREW,
WE GOTI'A GO!

01:52.760 --> 01:55.456
- HEY, SARAH, TELL HER
TO CHANGE IT UP, WILL YOU?

01:55.490 --> 01:56.889
IT'S THE SAME THING
OVER AND OVER AGAIN.

01:56.940 --> 01:58.589
- SAME WHAT?
WHAT SAME THING?

01:58.630 --> 02:00.484
- THE MUSIC.
- WHAT MUSIC?

02:00.530 --> 02:03.181
- THE SONG SHE WROTE
FOR THE THING.

02:03.220 --> 02:05.359
- THE SONG SHE WROTE
FOR THE THING?

02:05.400 --> 02:08.187
- WHAT THING?
- NOTHING. NOTHING.

02:08.230 --> 02:09.845
- WHAT IS THIS?

02:09.880 --> 02:12.223
- YOU WERE JUS'IY'EPSLAYING A SONG.

02:12.270 --> 02:14.226
- I UNDERSTAND
IT'S FOR A THING.

02:16.720 --> 02:20.167
- FINE.
I AM PLAYING THREE SONGS

02:20.200 --> 02:22.339
AT AN OPEN-MIC NIGHT

02:22.380 --> 02:24.541
AT A VERY, VERY SMALL CLUB.

02:24.590 --> 02:26.865
I DON'T NEED ANY ADVICE.
YOU CAN'T COME.

02:26.900 --> 02:29.585
THANKS FOR NOTHING.
SEE YOU LATER.

02:29.630 --> 02:31.279
- I'M GOING.
- WE'RE ALL GOING.

02:31.320 --> 02:34.699
- YEAH. HEY, UH, AMBER...

02:34.740 --> 02:36.492
I KNOW SOME BYRDS TUNES!

02:39.600 --> 02:41.909
- WOW. LOOK WHO IT IS.
- I KNOW.

02:41.950 --> 02:43.770
- WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?
- SORRY.

02:43.810 --> 02:45.949
- IT'S OKAY.
JUST GRAB A BOX.

02:45.990 --> 02:50.222
- I ALREADY--YEAH.

02:50.270 --> 02:51.817
- SO WHERE YOU BEEN?

02:51.860 --> 02:54.886
- UM, JUST, YOU KNOW,
SCHOOL STUFF.

02:54.930 --> 02:57.967
- SCHOOL STUFF?
- YEAH.

02:58.000 --> 03:01.686
S.A.T.s AND, UH, YOU KNOW,
STUDENT COUNCIL.

03:01.730 --> 03:03.550
IT'S STUPID STUFF.

03:03.590 --> 03:05.273
- IT'S NOT STUPID.

03:05.320 --> 03:08.972
- WELL, IT'S STUPID THAT,

03:09.010 --> 03:12.252
YOU KNOW, I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO BE HERE WITH YOU.

03:14.360 --> 03:16.669
- OKAY,
THAT'S PRE'ITY STUPID.

03:16.710 --> 03:20.498
- SO THERE WE GO.
WE AGREE.

03:20.540 --> 03:23.532
- YOU KNOW WHAT YOU NEED?
YOU NEED A NIGHT OFF--

03:23.580 --> 03:26.925
JUST A BREAK FROM EVERYTHING
THAT'S GOING ON.

03:26.960 --> 03:28.188
AND I'VE BEEN SO RUDE.

03:28.240 --> 03:30.891
I HAVEN'T EVEN HAD A CHANCE
TO TAKE YOU OUT ON A REAL DATE.

03:30.930 --> 03:32.921
- I MEAN, THAT'S TRUE.

03:32.970 --> 03:34.414
- SO I'M THINKING
A NIGHT OFF--

03:34.450 --> 03:37.829
NO S.A.T.s, NO A.A.,

03:37.870 --> 03:40.247
JUST YOU AND ME HAVING
SOME GOOD, OLD-FASHIONED FUN--

03:40.280 --> 03:44.592
MOVIES, ICE CREAM,
FOOD.

03:44.630 --> 03:47.940
WHAT I'M ASKING YOU IS...

03:47.980 --> 03:50.460
WILL YOU GO OUT WITH ME?

03:53.400 --> 03:55.607
YES, NO, MAYBE?
- I MEAN...

03:55.640 --> 03:57.574
YEAH, OKAY.

04:07.030 --> 04:10.614
- CAN I HELP YOU?
- YES!

04:10.660 --> 04:15.484
I'M LOOKING FOR, UM,
ADAM BR--BRAVERMAN.

04:15.530 --> 04:17.486
- YEAH, THAT'S ME.
WHAT DO YOU GOT FOR ME?

04:17.530 --> 04:19.350
- GOT FOR YOU?
- YEAH.

04:19.390 --> 04:21.278
I ASSUME YOU'RE NOT DELIVERING
THE SKATEBOARD,

04:21.330 --> 04:22.592
WHICH YOU CAN'T USE HERE,
BY THE WAY,

04:22.640 --> 04:23.800
NOT IN THE PARKING LOT,
ANYWHERE.

04:23.840 --> 04:26.400
- WHICH IS IRONIC,
SINCE WE STARTED OFF

04:26.430 --> 04:29.058
AS A SURF AND SKATEBOARD
APPAREL COMPANY.

04:29.090 --> 04:31.775
- "WE STARTED OFF"?

04:31.820 --> 04:34.641
YOU'RE NOT A DELIVERY GUY,
ARE YOU?

04:34.680 --> 04:37.547
- CORY SMITH.
- NEW BOSS.

04:37.580 --> 04:40.299
PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

04:40.340 --> 04:42.547
- OKAY.
- AH, SORRY.

04:42.590 --> 04:44.558
- WELL, NO, THAT'S FINE.
WE CAN WORK ON IT, MAN.

04:44.590 --> 04:45.864
- OKAY, WE'LL DO THAT.
- YEAH.

04:45.900 --> 04:48.869
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

04:48.900 --> 04:51.073
MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

04:51.110 --> 04:53.624
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

04:53.670 --> 04:55.900
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

04:55.950 --> 04:58.839
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

04:58.880 --> 05:00.609
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

05:00.640 --> 05:03.017
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:03.060 --> 05:05.608
FOREVER YOUNG

05:05.650 --> 05:08.471
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

05:08.510 --> 05:10.922
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

05:10.960 --> 05:12.928
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

05:12.960 --> 05:15.588
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

05:15.620 --> 05:18.066
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

05:18.110 --> 05:20.101
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

05:20.140 --> 05:22.131
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:22.180 --> 05:24.967
FOREVER YOUNG

05:25.010 --> 05:27.387
MAY YOU STAY

05:27.430 --> 05:30.422
FOREVER YOUNG

05:34.570 --> 05:36.083
- ARE YOU SURE
THIS IS GONNA BE ENOUGH FOOD?

05:36.120 --> 05:37.815
BECAUSE I MADE THESE
RESERVATIONS AT MONTICELLI'S.

05:37.850 --> 05:39.397
- DOS, LUPE, POR FAVOR.

05:39.440 --> 05:41.988
YEAH, MAN, I CANNOT STAND
SITTING THAT LONG.

05:42.030 --> 05:44.362
UH, BUT, DUDE, JUST WAIT

05:44.410 --> 05:47.857
FOR THESE FISH TACOS--
ABSOLUTELY KILL IT.

05:47.890 --> 05:49.824
- ALL RIGHT.

05:53.870 --> 05:55.588
- YEAH.

05:55.630 --> 05:58.929
ALL RIGHT, SO WHAT
WERE YOU SAYING ABOUT COLLEGE?

05:58.970 --> 06:00.790
STOKED?
- RIGHT. STOKED.

06:00.840 --> 06:04.492
SO I WAS SUPPOSED TO BE STUDYING
FOR THIS ECON FINAL, RIGHT?

06:04.530 --> 06:05.519
- MM-HMM.

06:05.570 --> 06:08.016
- BUT WHEN I FINALLY SAT DOWN
AT MY COMPUTER,

06:08.050 --> 06:09.631
MY ROOMMATE HAD LEFI'
THE PAGE OPEN

06:09.670 --> 06:10.773
TO THE LEGEND OF JOHNNY.

06:10.810 --> 06:12.437
IT'S LIKE A STUPID GAME.

06:12.470 --> 06:15.507
DUDE, THE NEXT THING I KNOW,
IT'S 5:00 IN THE MORNING,

06:15.540 --> 06:17.849
AND I HAVEN'T STOPPED PLAYING.
- RIGHT.

06:17.890 --> 06:21.508
- AND THAT WAS MY, LIKE,
AHA MOMENT, YOU KNOW?

06:21.550 --> 06:23.063
- UH-HUH.
- SO I GOT THINKING.

06:23.100 --> 06:26.991
YOU KNOW, IF A SMART DUDE
LIKE ME COULD SPEND SEVEN HOURS

06:27.040 --> 06:28.484
ON A DUMB GAME,

06:28.520 --> 06:30.829
JUST THINK
ABOUT WHAT A SMART GAME

06:30.870 --> 06:33.907
WOULD DO FOR DUMB DUDES.

06:33.940 --> 06:35.976
- I CAN'T IMAGINE.

06:36.010 --> 06:38.661
- BOOM. THAT'S WHAT.

06:38.700 --> 06:41.009
AND I HAVE THE CAPITAL
TO SAVE YOUR SHOE COMPANY.

06:41.050 --> 06:43.086
- YEAH. HEY, YOU KNOW,
THAT'S A PERFECT SEGUE,

06:43.120 --> 06:44.940
BECAUSE I REALLY DO WANT
TO HEAR, UH--

06:44.990 --> 06:45.911
- GO ON.

06:45.950 --> 06:47.531
- UH, I WANT TO HEAR
WHAT YOUR VISION IS

06:47.570 --> 06:48.958
FOR THE COMPANY,
YOU KNOW?

06:48.990 --> 06:50.639
- OKAY, THE SCROLL WHEEL
CONTROLS YOUR POWER.

06:50.680 --> 06:51.954
- OKAY, UH...

06:51.990 --> 06:53.673
- YOU KNOW,
T&S USED TO BE COOL.

06:53.720 --> 06:55.028
I WANT IT TO BE COOL AGAIN,

06:55.060 --> 06:56.755
BUT IT'S, LIKE,
SOMEWHERE ALONG THE LINE,

06:56.790 --> 06:58.610
YOU GUYS FORGOT YOUR ROOTS.

06:58.650 --> 07:00.618
GET THAT POWER-UP.
- UH, OKAY.

07:00.660 --> 07:02.867
- YOU GUYS GOT WEIRD IN '99.
- WE GOT WEIRD?

07:02.900 --> 07:04.868
- YEAH.
- IN '99, SPECIFICALLY...

07:04.900 --> 07:06.549
WE GOT WEIRD?
- YEAH. TAKE THAT TRAP DOOR.

07:06.590 --> 07:07.386
- ALL RIGHT.
- RUN! RUN, RUN, RUN!

07:07.420 --> 07:08.933
- I'M GOING. I'M GOING.
I'M GOING.

07:08.980 --> 07:11.972
[children shouting song]

07:17.090 --> 07:18.637
- GUYS, YOU DON'T NEED
TO BANG--

07:18.670 --> 07:20.706
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE PANNING
FOR GOLD.

07:20.750 --> 07:22.536
[children continue
shouting song]

07:22.580 --> 07:25.219
GUYS...
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

07:25.270 --> 07:27.226
YOU'RE GETTING READY,
RIGHT?

07:27.270 --> 07:29.500
AND ONE, TWO, THREE.

07:29.550 --> 07:32.235
- THIS IS...
- A DISASTER.

07:32.270 --> 07:34.966
- ALL RIGHT, I WANT
ALL THE GIRLS TO GO TO THE LEFT

07:35.000 --> 07:37.059
AND ALL THE BOYS TO GO
TO THE RIGHT ON MY COUNT.

07:37.110 --> 07:38.589
- MR. CROSBY.
- OKAY?

07:38.630 --> 07:40.586
HOLD ON ONE SECOND, OKAY?
- MR. CROSBY.

07:40.630 --> 07:43.667
- FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.
- MR. CROSBY. MR. CROSBY.

07:43.700 --> 07:45.668
- ALL RIGHT, WHAT IS IT?
WHAT IS IT? WHAT IS IT?

07:45.700 --> 07:47.179
- I HAVE TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

07:47.220 --> 07:51.281
- OKAY, YOU CAN GO.
- I JUST DID.

07:51.330 --> 07:53.981
- OH, MY GOSH.
UM...

07:54.020 --> 07:56.818
[children shouting
and laughing]

07:56.850 --> 07:59.501
EVERYONE JUST STAY THERE,
I GUESS.

07:59.540 --> 08:04.614
I DON'T KNOW. UM, GREAT.
YOU GUYS ARE HERE FOR THIS.

08:04.650 --> 08:06.231
JUST WHAT I WANTED.
- ARE YOU GONNA STOP THAT?

08:06.270 --> 08:08.579
- WHAT?
[both chuckle]

08:08.620 --> 08:11.919
- BLEEKER BEIGE.

08:11.970 --> 08:14.063
HEY, HONEY.
[footsteps on stairs]

08:14.110 --> 08:16.726
HI.
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

08:16.770 --> 08:18.795
HADDIE!
- WHAT?

08:18.840 --> 08:20.239
- PLEASE COME HERE.

08:20.290 --> 08:21.734
I DON'T WANT
TO RAISE MY VOICE,

08:21.770 --> 08:23.761
BECAUSE I'M REALLY EXCITED
ABOUT THIS.

08:23.810 --> 08:26.734
LISTEN, YOU KNOW
HOW WE'VE TALKED ABOUT BEFORE

08:26.780 --> 08:27.917
REDOING YOUR ROOM

08:27.950 --> 08:30.601
AND, YOU KNOW, PAINTING
OVER THE PINK--

08:30.640 --> 08:33.200
- MOM, WHY ARE YOU TALKING
ABOUT THIS?

08:33.230 --> 08:35.266
I DON'T CARE ABOUT MY ROOM
RIGHT NOW.

08:35.300 --> 08:37.268
- HONEY, IT'S NOT JUST
ABOUT THAT.

08:37.300 --> 08:40.019
I'M ACKNOWLEDGING THE FACT
THAT YOU'RE GROWING UP.

08:40.070 --> 08:41.753
- YOU CAN'T JUST BRIBE ME

08:41.790 --> 08:43.963
AND MAKE EVERYTHING OKAY
BY PAINTING MY ROOM.

08:44.000 --> 08:45.103
YOU CAN'T FIX IT LIKE THIS.

08:45.140 --> 08:46.619
- I'M NOT TRYING
TO BRIBE YOU, HONEY.

08:46.660 --> 08:50.278
I'M NOT. I JUST THINK
THIS COULD BE REALLY FUN.

08:50.320 --> 08:52.868
AND IT'S NOT A BRIBE.
I DON'T BRIBE.

08:52.910 --> 08:55.663
MAYBE IT'S A LITTLE BIT
OF A BRIBE.

08:57.190 --> 09:01.775
WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT NANTUCKET GREEN, HUH?

09:01.810 --> 09:03.801
- I-I AM--I'M MAD AT YOU.

09:03.850 --> 09:06.296
- YOU CAN BE MAD AT ME.
BE SO MAD AT ME.

09:06.330 --> 09:08.366
WE'RE GONNA HAVE FUN
DOING IT.

09:08.400 --> 09:10.709
I'LL SMILE,
AND YOU CAN BE MAD.

09:10.750 --> 09:11.921
YOU CAN PICK OUT A COLOR.

09:11.960 --> 09:14.645
I'VE GOT BLEEKER BEIGE,
AND THESE PA'I'I'ERNS

09:14.690 --> 09:19.309
OF THESE CHINESE CHESTNUT
WALL MOUNTS ARE REALLY FUN.

09:19.350 --> 09:20.999
- FINE. YEAH. OKAY.

09:21.040 --> 09:23.201
I'LL DO IT.
THANKS, I GUESS.

09:23.250 --> 09:25.309
- GREAT.

09:25.350 --> 09:27.284
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

09:30.390 --> 09:33.564
- [humming softly]

09:35.710 --> 09:38.702
[knock at door]

09:38.750 --> 09:41.742
- OH, HEY. DO YOU HAVE ANY,
UM, WHITES?

09:41.780 --> 09:45.159
I'M DOING SOME WHITES.
- REALLY?

09:45.200 --> 09:47.122
- YEAH.
- THAT MAKES ME NERVOUS.

09:47.170 --> 09:49.638
BUT, YEAH, ACTUALLY, I DO,
IF YOU'RE GONNA DO SOME LAUNDRY.

09:49.690 --> 09:54.275
I HAVE A BIG PILE
OF DIRTY, SMELLY LAUNDRY.

09:54.310 --> 09:55.868
JUST GO AHEAD AND SCOOP IT UP
WITH YOUR HANDS

09:55.900 --> 09:57.128
AND THEN WASH IT.

09:57.180 --> 09:58.693
- I DON'T REALLY WANT
TO DO ANY LAUNDRY.

09:58.730 --> 10:00.072
I'M JUST COMING IN HERE
SO YOU'LL PLAY ME A SONG.

10:00.110 --> 10:01.930
- YEAH. I WON'T.
- COME ON.

10:01.980 --> 10:03.868
WHY NOT?
- BECAUSE IT'S PERSONAL.

10:03.910 --> 10:05.764
AND--AND I JUST DON'T--

10:05.810 --> 10:07.869
- WELL, YOU'RE ABOUT TO MAKE
THE PERSONAL VERY PUBLIC,

10:07.910 --> 10:09.730
SO MAYBE YOU, YOU KNOW...
- IT'S EMBARRASSING.

10:09.780 --> 10:11.702
AND I FEEL NERVOUS
AND STUFF.

10:11.740 --> 10:13.219
- I UNDERSTAND.

10:13.260 --> 10:15.194
YOUR DAD USED TO PLAY STUFF
FOR ME, YOU KNOW,

10:15.230 --> 10:18.711
BEFORE IT WAS READY,
AND H WAS PRETI'Y HELPFUL.

10:18.750 --> 10:22.379
- WELL, DAD AND YOU
DIDN'T REALLY TURN OUT SO WELL,

10:22.410 --> 10:26.096
SO MAYBE--MAYBE
WE SHOULDN'T JINX IT.

10:28.170 --> 10:30.968
- NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT DIDN'T TURN OUT SO WELL.

10:31.000 --> 10:35.767
BUT HE'S A VERY GOOD MUSICIAN,
AND SO ARE YOU.

10:35.800 --> 10:38.769
COME ON.

10:41.460 --> 10:44.088
I'LL PLAY SOME FOR YOU,
BUT YOU HAVE TO JUST--

10:44.120 --> 10:45.849
- NO, BE COOL.
NO, I KNOW.

10:45.880 --> 10:50.431
AGAIN, I'VE BEEN IN THE WORLD.
YES, I KNOW HOW TO BE COOL.

11:05.000 --> 11:08.072
- [hums softly]
WHAT?

11:08.110 --> 11:09.964
- NOTHING.
I CAN'T SEE YOUR FACE.

11:10.010 --> 11:13.969
I WI--SORRY.
JUST START AGAIN.

11:17.810 --> 11:19.425
- OKAY, IT'S LIKE...

11:19.470 --> 11:21.358
IT GOES LIKE...

11:21.400 --> 11:24.949
[humming softly]

11:28.920 --> 11:31.195
WHAT?
- WHAT'S IT CALLED?

11:31.240 --> 11:32.889
- IT'S CALLED GRAVEYARD SONG.

11:32.930 --> 11:35.512
WHAT?
- [laughs] NOTHING.

11:35.550 --> 11:37.723
I MEAN, YOU'LL BRING THE CROWD
TO THEIR FEET.

11:37.760 --> 11:40.888
- SORRY, I'M NOT REALLY READY
FOR THIS.

11:40.940 --> 11:42.248
- I'M TRYING TO LIGHTEN
THE MOOD.

11:42.280 --> 11:44.145
