YOU--YOU GOT TO COME BACK.

22:15.360 --> 22:17.419
IF YOU DON'T,
THIS--THIS PLAY'S GONNA BE

22:18.820 --> 22:23.473
SINCE THE EARTHQUAKE
OF 1905.

22:23.510 --> 22:25.740
190--1906?
- 6.

22:25.790 --> 22:27.758
- MAN, THE PLAY'S
ABOUT THE HISTORY OF CALIFORNIA.

22:27.790 --> 22:29.758
I DON'T EVEN KNOW.
- [sighs]

22:29.790 --> 22:32.418
- JOE, YOU GOT TO COME BACK.
- I DON'T KNOW, MAN. I JUST--

22:32.450 --> 22:36.136
- I'M NOT EQUIPPED TO DO THIS
WITHOUT YOU.

22:36.180 --> 22:40.935
- YEAH, I GOT--I GOT TO THINK
ABOUT IT A LITTLE.

22:40.980 --> 22:43.551
- OKAY.
- YEAH.

22:43.600 --> 22:46.660
CROSBY?
- YEAH?

22:46.710 --> 22:48.086
- I JUST--

22:48.120 --> 22:52.489
I AM KIDDING, MAN.

22:52.540 --> 22:54.019
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'RE KIDDING?

22:54.060 --> 22:56.437
- YOUR SISTER TOLD ME
YOU'D BE COMING OVER.

22:56.470 --> 22:57.505
- SHE TOLD YOU
THAT I WAS COMING OVER?

22:57.540 --> 22:58.746
- I HEARD YOUR BIKE.

22:58.790 --> 23:00.610
- AND THEN YOU JUST LET ME
GO THROUGH THAT WHOLE SPEECH?

23:00.650 --> 23:02.572
- IT WAS A GREAT SPEECH.

23:02.620 --> 23:04.201
- THEN I TAKE IT ALL BACK.
- YOU CAN'T TAKE IT BACK.

23:04.240 --> 23:05.059
- NO, I DO.
- IT'S OUT THERE.

23:05.100 --> 23:06.169
GET IN HERE
AND HAVE A BEER WITH ME.

23:06.210 --> 23:08.963
- I DIDN'T MEAN ANY OF IT.
- I WANT TO SEE YOU DO

23:09.000 --> 23:10.103
THAT WHOLE THING AGAIN.

23:10.140 --> 23:11.960
WHAT WAS THE PART ABOUT YOU
DESPERATELY NEEDING ME?

23:12.010 --> 23:14.797
[Das Racists' Combination
Pizza Hut And Taco Bell]

23:14.840 --> 23:16.626
- WAIT, WHAT?
AT THE PIZZA HUT

23:16.670 --> 23:18.900
- WHAT?
- WHAT? AT THE TACO BELL

23:18.940 --> 23:22.489
- WHAT? THE COMBINATION
PIZZA HUT AND TACO BELL

23:22.530 --> 23:24.566
- WE AT THE PIZZA HUT
- NO

23:24.610 --> 23:26.419
- WE AT THIEIC'JI'ACO BELL

23:26.470 --> 23:28.119
- WE AT THE COMBINATION...

23:28.160 --> 23:31.778
- [sniffing]

23:31.820 --> 23:35.506
[loud music and chatter]

23:38.650 --> 23:41.471
- BRAVERMAN, COME HERE
A SEC, MAN.

23:41.520 --> 23:43.988
- I WANT ONE OF THOSE.
- CHECK THAT OUT.

23:44.040 --> 23:47.589
- CHECK OUT THIS ROBOT.
WHOO.

23:47.630 --> 23:51.452
- COOL. THAT'S RADICAL.

23:51.490 --> 23:53.492
UH, I DIDN'T THINK
YOU WERE COMING IN TODAY.

23:53.530 --> 23:55.566
- OH, YEAH, MAN,
WE JUST GOT HERE.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.147
CHECK IT.
THESE ARE A FEW OF MY PALS--

23:57.190 --> 24:00.603
SPIDER, TJ, SMOKEY.
- HEY, BRAVERMAN.

24:00.640 --> 24:02.460
- HI. SMOKEY.

24:02.510 --> 24:04.011
- SPIDER HERE HAS SOME REALLY
AMAZING SHOE IDEAS.

24:04.060 --> 24:05.539
SPIDER, TELL HIM.
- OKAY.

24:05.580 --> 24:07.502
- WELL, IT'S MORE OF A DRAWING
THAN AN IDEA,

24:07.540 --> 24:09.679
BUT YOU TAKE
ALL THE SHOE DEMONS

24:09.720 --> 24:12.473
OUT OF THE T&S THING...

24:12.520 --> 24:15.546
POW. KICKING A NEW FLAVOR.
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

24:15.590 --> 24:16.989
- PUT THAT ON THE SOLE.
"POW."

24:17.040 --> 24:18.177
- NO, THE "POW"
IS IN YOUR BRAIN.

24:18.210 --> 24:21.008
SEE, IT'S LIKE THE SKULL,
BRAVERMAN, WITH THE HORNS.

24:21.040 --> 24:22.894
THAT'S ACT UALLY--
THE SHOE IS THINKING THAT.

24:22.940 --> 24:25.215
- SHOE DEMONS EXITING.

24:25.250 --> 24:27.047
- IT'S LIKE
IT'S BEING EXORCISED.

24:27.080 --> 24:30.561
- IT'S BEING EXTRACTED.
- IT'S A SHOE, BRAVERMAN.

24:30.600 --> 24:32.215
- RIGHT.

24:32.260 --> 24:34.603
YEAH, WELL, YOU'VE GIVEN ME
A LOT TO THINK ABOUT.

24:34.640 --> 24:36.119
CORY, CAN I SEE YOU
IN MY OFFICE?

24:36.160 --> 24:38.958
- YEAH, MAN,
AS SOON AS I'M DONE HERE--

24:38.990 --> 24:40.571
- IT CAN'T WAIT.

24:40.610 --> 24:43.613
- UH-OH, BUSTED, CORY.
BUSTED.

24:43.650 --> 24:48.098
[laughter]

24:48.140 --> 24:51.655
- THANK YOU.

24:51.690 --> 24:53.032
WHAT'S UP?

24:53.070 --> 24:55.766
- LISTEN, I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU WORKED YOUR BUSINESS

24:55.800 --> 24:58.519
WITH THE VIDEO GAMES,
BUT THIS PLACE IS A LIVING,

24:58.560 --> 24:59.527
BREATHING COMPANY.

24:59.560 --> 25:00.595
WE MAKE SHOES.

25:00.630 --> 25:01.767
AND THERE ARE PEOPLE
WHO WORK HERE

25:01.810 --> 25:04.278
WHO NEED THIS COMPANY TO SUCCEED
WHETHER YOU DO OR NOT.

25:04.330 --> 25:06.184
- WAIT A MINUTE, OKAY?

25:06.220 --> 25:09.087
NO ONE WANTS T&S
TO BE GREAT AGAIN MORE ME.

25:09.120 --> 25:10.917
- REALLY? THEN I'D LIKE TO SEE
YOU ACT LIKE IT.

25:10.950 --> 25:12.770
STARTING TOMORROW, COME IN
DURING REGULAR BUSINESS HOURS.

25:12.820 --> 25:13.741
MEET YOUR DESIGN TEAM.

25:13.780 --> 25:15.953
THESE ARE GREAT PEOPLE
WITH GREAT IDEAS.

25:15.990 --> 25:17.548
THEY'RE ALSO PEOPLE
WITH FAMILIES

25:17.580 --> 25:19.093
WHO ARE SCARED TO DEATH
THAT YOU ARE GONNA RUN

25:19.130 --> 25:22.679
THIS PLACE
INTO THE GROUND.

25:22.720 --> 25:25.689
- IS THAT HOW YOU FEEL?

25:25.730 --> 25:26.867
- I DON'T KNOW YET.

25:26.900 --> 25:28.208
BUT Al-TER WHAT I JUST SAW
IN THERE,

25:28.250 --> 25:31.174
HONESTLY, THAT DOESN'T EVEN
BEGIN TO COVER MY FEARS.

25:31.210 --> 25:33.246
- I KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT I'M DOING.

25:33.290 --> 25:35.281
- OKAY, LISTEN, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

25:35.320 --> 25:37.003
YOU DON'T HAVE
A MISSION STATEMENT.

25:37.050 --> 25:38.312
YOU DON'T HAVE
A BUSINESS PLAN.

25:38.360 --> 25:40.328
THE ONLY THING
THAT YOU'VE PRESENTED ME WITH

25:40.360 --> 25:42.635
IS THIS VAGUE IDEA
THAT SOMEHOW WE GOT WEIRD

25:42.670 --> 25:43.841
IN THE '905.

25:43.880 --> 25:45.017
- I DON'T HAVE AN ANSWER YET.

25:45.060 --> 25:46.368
- WELL, YOU BETTER COME UP
WITH ONE SOON.

25:46.400 --> 25:47.367
YOU BOUGHT THE COMPANY.

25:47.400 --> 25:48.503
YOU'RE THE GUY
WHO HAS TO HAVE THE ANSWER.

25:48.540 --> 25:51.122
- I KNOW WHAT THE PROBLEM IS.
- WELL, WHAT'S THAT?

25:51.170 --> 25:54.571
- YOU GUYS STARTED
SELLING OUT.

25:54.620 --> 25:56.781
NOW, COMING UP
WITH WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO

25:56.830 --> 25:58.206
IS A CREATIVE PROBLEM.

25:58.240 --> 26:00.617
IT'S EXCITING,
AND I'M WORKING ON IT.

26:00.660 --> 26:05.029
AND H WANT YOU TO BE WORKING
ON IT, TOO, WITH ME.

26:05.080 --> 26:07.696
- THAT'S IT?
- YEAH.

26:07.730 --> 26:10.142
THAT'S HOW PEOPLE SOLVE
PROBLEMS.

26:10.180 --> 26:11.875
THEY THINK ABOUT THEM.

26:11.910 --> 26:14.595
YOU CAN'T CONTROL
CREATIVITY, MAN.

26:14.640 --> 26:16.949
NOW, I AM COMPLETELY COMFORTABLE
WITH THE FACT

26:16.980 --> 26:18.732
THAT I DON'T HAVE
AN ANSWER YET.

26:18.780 --> 26:21.704
BUT YOU NEED TO BE COMFORTABLE
WITH THAT, TOO,

26:21.750 --> 26:23.672
BECAUSE WHATEVER WE DO,

26:23.720 --> 26:26.336
IT'S GOING TO INVOLVE
TAKING RISKS.

26:29.410 --> 26:31.617
BRAVERMAN.

26:31.650 --> 26:34.995
BRAVERMAN.
BRAVER MAN.

26:35.040 --> 26:38.339
- YES, YES, THAT'S MY NAME.
- I LIKE YOU, OKAY?

26:38.380 --> 26:40.792
YOU'RE A COOL DUDE.

26:40.840 --> 26:43.968
YOU'RE SMART, AND I WANT YOU
TO STICK AROUND.

26:44.010 --> 26:46.387
BUT WE'RE GOING TO BE GOING
FOR AN EXTREMELY

26:46.430 --> 26:48.637
YOUTH-ORIENTED PRODUCT.

26:48.670 --> 26:51.776
AND IT IS GOING
TO GET RADICAL.

26:51.810 --> 26:56.122
AND I JUST WANT
TO MAKE SURE...

26:56.160 --> 26:58.742
THAT YOU'RE UP FOR IT.

27:01.680 --> 27:03.887
- OKAY.

27:03.930 --> 27:06.262
- ARE YOU SURE?

27:06.310 --> 27:08.824
- I'M SURE.

27:08.860 --> 27:11.681
- COOL.

27:19.490 --> 27:23.017
- [sighs]

27:27.090 --> 27:28.250
- WHAT'S THE DEAL
WITH THE MOVIE?

27:28.300 --> 27:29.255
HOW DID IT GO?

27:29.300 --> 27:30.562
- WE WENT TO THE U.A. BERKELEY 7
ON SHATTUCK.

27:30.610 --> 27:33.056
AND I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT THEY
RAISED THE TICKET PRICES AGAIN.

27:33.090 --> 27:35.672
- AWFUL. SO RUDE. AND WHAT DID
YOU THINK ABOUT THE MOVIE?

27:35.720 --> 27:37.051
HOW DID YOU FEEL?
- WELL, I MEAN, IT WAS OKAY.

27:37.100 --> 27:38.431
BUT MICHAEL CERA
WAS OBVIOUSLY HILARIOUS.

27:38.480 --> 27:40.129
- OBVIOUSLY HILARIOUS
AND CUTE.

27:40.170 --> 27:42.445
- AND ADORABLE.
- YES. CORRECT.

27:42.480 --> 27:44.107
OKAY.
- OKAY, I THINK YOU GOT IT.

27:44.140 --> 27:46.244
THAT'S PRETTY MUCH
ALL THE BASES COVERED.

27:46.280 --> 27:48.726
- HOW DO I LOOK?

27:48.770 --> 27:51.079
- YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

27:51.110 --> 27:53.214
- [laughs]
THANK YOU.

27:53.250 --> 27:54.933
THANK YOU, SERIOUSLY,
FOR EVERYTHING.

27:54.980 --> 27:56.971
I WILL CALL YOU
WHEN IT'S TIME TO PICK ME UP.

27:57.020 --> 27:58.419
- CAN I SAY SOMETHING,

27:58.460 --> 28:00.257
EVEN THOUGH
YOU'RE GONNA GET MAD AT ME?

28:00.290 --> 28:02.770
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

28:02.810 --> 28:04.459
DRINKING...

28:04.510 --> 28:06.887
I KNOW. BUT I JUST NEED
TO GET IT OUT.

28:06.920 --> 28:09.889
YOU KNOW THAT MY DAD DRANK,
AND IT WAS A BIG PROBLEM.

28:09.920 --> 28:11.956
- MM-HMM.
- OKAY.

28:12.000 --> 28:14.753
IT'S JUST THAT WHEN SOMEBODY
YOU LOVE DRINKS,

28:14.790 --> 28:17.998
IT'S LIKE THEY'RE
A DIFFERENT PERSON,

28:18.040 --> 28:19.109
AND YOU DON'T MATTER.

28:19.140 --> 28:21.859
AND IT CAN BE REALLY,
REALLY SCARY.

28:21.900 --> 28:23.515
AND I-I-I UNDERSTAND
THAT THIS GUY

28:23.560 --> 28:26.723
IS PROBABLY THE COOLEST GUY
IN THE WHOLE WORLD,

28:26.770 --> 28:29.807
AND I'M SURE IT WILL NEVER
BE A PROBLEM, HONESTLY.

28:29.840 --> 28:32.809
- ALEX IS OKAY.
- I KNOW. I KNOW.

28:32.840 --> 28:34.114
- HE'S BEEN SOBER
FOR SIX MONTHS.

28:34.160 --> 28:36.014
- I KNOW. BUT THAT'S NOT
VERY LONG.

28:36.050 --> 28:38.359
MY DAD WOULD HAVE LONGER
STRETCHES AND GO BACK INTO IT.

28:38.400 --> 28:39.742
I'M JUST SAYING.

28:39.780 --> 28:42.465
- I KNOW. I'M--I HEAR YOU.
I UNDERSTAND.

28:42.510 --> 28:45.297
- JUST BE AWARE, OKAY?

28:45.340 --> 28:47.194
OKAY?
- OKAY.

28:47.240 --> 28:49.549
- YEAH.
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY.

28:49.580 --> 28:52.378
YOU'RE MY RIDE HOME.
- VERY COMFORTING.

28:52.420 --> 28:54.376
OKAY, GREAT. I'LL CALL YOU.
THANK YOU.

28:54.420 --> 28:57.867
I AM LISTENING TO YOU.
- GO GET HIM.

28:57.900 --> 28:59.003
YOU LOOK GREAT.
- THANK YOU.

28:59.040 --> 29:01.861
- HE'S A LUCKY MAN.

29:09.020 --> 29:10.567
- UH-OH.
[chuckles]

29:10.610 --> 29:11.804
SHOULD I BE WORRIED?

29:11.850 --> 29:13.329
YOU'RE SITTING ALONE
IN THE DARK

29:13.370 --> 29:16.533
IN THE LAUNDRY ROOM
NOT DOING LAUNDRY?

29:16.580 --> 29:19.879
- I JUST CAN'T FIGURE OUT
HOW TO GET MY WHITES WHITER.

29:19.930 --> 29:22.956
- WHAT'S UP?
- OH, MOM.

29:23.000 --> 29:24.854
DO YOU EVER WORRY SO MUCH
ABOUT SOMETHING BAD

29:24.900 --> 29:26.470
HAPPENING TO ME
THAT YOU STOMPED OUT MY FIRE

29:26.520 --> 29:27.544
BY ACCIDENT?

29:27.590 --> 29:29.137
- I DON'T KNOW.

29:29.180 --> 29:32.069
YOU KNOW, WE ALL TRY
TO PROTECT OUR KIDS.

29:32.110 --> 29:33.520
IT'S WHAT WE DO.

29:33.560 --> 29:34.766
- MM-HMM.

29:34.800 --> 29:37.598
- THEN THEY GROW UP, AND WE
CAN'T PROTECT THEM ANYMORE.

29:37.630 --> 29:39.871
AND YOU'D SAVE YOURSELF
A LOT OF GRIEF

29:39.910 --> 29:41.070
IF YOU'D ACCEPT THAT FACT.

29:41.120 --> 29:44.248
I MEAN, WE CAN BE THERE
FOR THEM,

29:44.290 --> 29:46.565
BUT...

29:46.610 --> 29:50.057
WE CAN'T PROTECT THEM.

29:50.090 --> 29:51.842
I THINK IT'S ONE
OF THE TOUGHEST THINGS

29:51.890 --> 29:54.051
ABOUT BEING A PARENT.

30:01.620 --> 30:03.793
[door opens]

30:07.250 --> 30:10.595
- HEY.

30:10.630 --> 30:14.043
WHAT YOU READING?

30:14.080 --> 30:16.082
- IT'S A BOOK.

30:20.470 --> 30:24.156
- ALL RIGHT, WELL, I JUST CAME
TO SAY GOOD NIGHT, MAX.

30:24.200 --> 30:26.953
DID I EVER TELL YOU
YOU'RE A GOOD KID?

30:26.990 --> 30:28.878
- MM-HMM.

30:28.930 --> 30:30.989
- WELL, YOU STILL ARE.

30:37.930 --> 30:42.173
- WHY ARE YOU STILL HERE?

30:42.210 --> 30:46.169
- JUST LOST IN THOUGHT, I GUESS.
I'M JUST...

30:46.220 --> 30:49.633
I THINK MY BOSS
THINKS I'M TOO OLD.

30:49.670 --> 30:52.912
- HOW OLDHARE YOU?

30:52.950 --> 30:56.875
- THAT'S PRETTY OLD.

30:56.920 --> 30:59.468
- SWEET DREAMS, SON.

31:02.200 --> 31:03.474
- ARE WE NOT ALLOWED
TO BE OUT HERE?

31:03.510 --> 31:04.920
- WELL, IF I SAID
WE HAD PERMISSION,

31:04.960 --> 31:06.029
WILL IT MAKE IT
ANY LESS EXCITING?

31:06.070 --> 31:08.516
- NO. ACTUALLY, I'M VERY AFRAID
OF BREAKING RULES,

31:08.550 --> 31:12.862
WHICH IS STUPID, BUT--
OH, MY GOD.

31:15.210 --> 31:19.556
THIS IS BEAUTIFUL.

31:19.600 --> 31:21.215
WHAT IS THIS?

31:21.250 --> 31:24.947
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
HOW DID YOU SET ALL OF THIS UP?

31:24.980 --> 31:26.117
- I PULLED SOME STRINGS,

31:26.160 --> 31:28.663
YOU KNOW,
CALLED IN A FEW FAVORS.

31:28.710 --> 31:31.326
- THIS IS MY FAVORITE MOVIE.
- IT'S YOUR THIRD FAVORITE.

31:31.370 --> 31:32.632
YOUR FIRST IS LOVE ACTUALLY.

31:32.680 --> 31:34.056
BUT YOU ALREADY SAW IT
WITH THAT STEVE GUY,

31:34.090 --> 31:36.024
SO THAT WAS COMPLETELY OUT
OF THE QUESTION.

31:36.060 --> 31:37.027
- MM-HMM.

31:37.060 --> 31:38.470
- AND ALTHOUGH I LIKE YOU,

31:38.510 --> 31:40.330
NOT ENOUGH
TO SIT THROUGH TWILIGHT.

31:40.380 --> 31:42.996
- [laughs] I MEAN,
I JUST DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

31:44.480 --> 31:46.482
- I TRY.

31:46.520 --> 31:48.033
COME ON.

31:48.070 --> 31:50.129
WE'RE MISSING THE MOVIE.

31:50.180 --> 31:52.933
- OKAY.

31:52.980 --> 31:55.448
SO CUTE.
WHERE DID YOU GET THIS?

31:55.490 --> 31:58.630
I, UH, CALLED IN
SOME FAVORS.

31:58.670 --> 32:00.945
IF YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,
I'M VERY WELL CONNECTED.

32:00.980 --> 32:02.948
- TO...?

32:02.990 --> 32:05.436
- THE SECURITY GUARD.
HE OWES ME A FAVOR.

32:05.470 --> 32:08.155
- OOH.
SPARKLING WATER.

32:08.200 --> 32:09.508
- SO HOW ABOUT WE TOAST?

32:09.540 --> 32:11.337
- OKAY.

32:11.370 --> 32:13.543
- TO FIRST DATES.

32:13.580 --> 32:15.024
- OKAY.

32:15.070 --> 32:16.230
[Stars' Undertow]

32:16.270 --> 32:19.137
- ALL THE WIND'S
AT YOUR EYES

32:19.170 --> 32:21.058
AT YOUR EYES,
AT YOUR EYES

32:21.110 --> 32:22.725
AT YOUR EYES
- THIS IS GOOD.

32:28.460 --> 32:31.668
BOTH TAKE YOU
TO THE FLOOR...

32:31.700 --> 32:34.589
- THANK YOU.

32:34.640 --> 32:36.221
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

32:36.260 --> 32:38.046
- TO THE FLOOR
- WHEN WILL IT STOP?

32:38.090 --> 32:42.299
WHEN WILL IT STOP?
WHEN WILL IT STOP?

32:42.330 --> 32:44.673
WHEN WILL IT STOP?

32:54.730 --> 32:56.516
- HOW WAS THE MOVIE?

32:56.560 --> 32:58.039
- HEY.

32:58.070 --> 33:00.527
UH, IT WAS GOOD.
IT WAS A LITTLE LONG.

33:00.560 --> 33:03.074
BUT MICHAEL CERA
WAS ADORABLE AS ALWAYS.

33:03.110 --> 33:06.386
[continues playing guitar]

33:06.430 --> 33:07.385
WHAT?

33:07.430 --> 33:10.467
- YOU STILL PLAY THAT CHORD
THAT FUNNY WAY.

33:10.500 --> 33:12.320
- I KNOW.

33:12.360 --> 33:13.804
DAD SHOWED ME HOW TO DO IT,

33:13.850 --> 33:16.296
AND NOW IT'S THE ONLY WAY
I CAN PLAY IT.

33:16.330 --> 33:18.082
- NO, I REMEMBER.

33:18.130 --> 33:19.643
YOU WERE SO LITTLE
WHEN YOU STARTED PLAYING,

33:19.680 --> 33:24.379
AND YOUR LITTLE, TINY
LITTLE HAND WOULDN'T REACH.

33:26.790 --> 33:29.099
- YEAH, AND NOW I GET
MADE FUN OF.

33:29.140 --> 33:32.246
- WELL, SOMETHING USEFUL
HE TAUGHT YOU, ANYWAY.

33:32.280 --> 33:35.169
- YEAH.

33:35.220 --> 33:38.178
- I'M SORRY YOU'RE NOT DOING
THE OPEN-MIC NIGHT.

33:38.220 --> 33:41.109
I FEEL BAD ABOUT THAT.

33:43.400 --> 33:46.153
YOU KNOW, WHEN YOU HAVE KIDS,

33:46.190 --> 33:48.055
IF YOU HAVE KIDS,

33:48.090 --> 33:51.196
THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU SHOULD KNOW--

33:51.230 --> 33:55.121
A VERY CONFUSING THING
THEY DON'T TELL YOU.

33:55.170 --> 33:59.163
YOU SEE SO MUCH
OF YOURSELF IN THEM.

33:59.200 --> 34:02.089
YOU SEE...

34:02.140 --> 34:04.233
YOUR...

34:04.280 --> 34:07.101
IRONIC TAKE ON THE WORLD.

34:07.140 --> 34:08.584
- THAT ONE WAS FOR ME.

34:08.630 --> 34:11.246
- YOU SEE YOUR SMILE,
YOUR WALK,

34:11.290 --> 34:13.758
YOUR SENSE OF HUMOR,
WHATEVER.

34:13.810 --> 34:16.074
AND YOU THINK...

34:16.120 --> 34:19.214
THEY'RE YOU.

34:19.260 --> 34:22.878
BUT THEY'RE NOT YOU.

34:22.920 --> 34:26.879
AND THEY SHOULDN'T HAVE
ALL OF YOUR BAGGAGE,

34:26.920 --> 34:29.195
YOUR FEAR,
AND YOUR INSECURITY,

34:29.230 --> 34:32.199
AND YOUR LIFE EXPERIENCE,
BECAUSE THAT'S NOT FAIR.

34:32.240 --> 34:35.824
THEY HAVE THEIR OWN.

34:35.860 --> 34:39.444
YOUR SONG IS BEAUTIFUL.

34:39.490 --> 34:41.867
IT'S HAUNTING AND MOVING,

34:41.900 --> 34:45.904
AND...

34:45.940 --> 34:47.862
IT'S SO YOU.

34:47.910 --> 34:52.802
AND THAT'S ALL I SHOULD'VE SAID
TO YOU THE OTHER NIGHT.

34:52.840 --> 34:55.115
I'M SO PROUD,
AND I'M SO IMPRESSED,

34:55.160 --> 34:58.254
AND I'M SO...

34:58.300 --> 35:01.269
IN AWE OF YOU.

35:03.820 --> 35:07.756
AND I WANT YOU TO JUST
GO OUT THERE AND...

35:07.790 --> 35:09.712
FLY.

35:11.520 --> 35:14.375
YOU CAN FLY.

35:25.640 --> 35:28.211
- HEY, GUYS, GUYS, CAN I HAVE
EVERYONE'S ATTENTION?

35:28.260 --> 35:30.399
I HAVE A HUGE SURPRISE
FOR YOU.

35:30.430 --> 35:32.182
[children shouting]

35:32.230 --> 35:33.606
OKAY, HOLD ON. HOLD ON.
HOLD ON.

35:33.640 --> 35:36.814
OUR MOST TALENTED DIRECTOR
IS BACK FROM VACATION.

35:36.850 --> 35:40.263
YOU MAY REMEMBER HIM--
SYDNEY'S DAD, JOEL!

35:40.310 --> 35:44.588
[cheers and applause]

35:46.970 --> 35:49.416
- HI, DADDY.
- HEY, HONEY.

35:49.450 --> 35:52.658
WHO WANTS TO HELP US
TELL A STORY?

35:52.700 --> 35:55.726
SIT ON YOUR TUSHIES
IF YOU CAN HEAR ME.

35:55.770 --> 36:00.423
NOW, WE'RE GONNA NEED
TWO SUPER-SPECIAL VOLUNTEERS

36:00.460 --> 36:05.227
TO HELP US PASS OUT
A NEW SCRIPT

36:05.260 --> 36:07.876
FEATURING ALL THE MUSIC
THAT CROSBY TAUGHT YOU--

36:07.920 --> 36:12.198
ALL THAT GREAT MUSIC
WITH SOME HISTORY OF CALIFORNIA.

36:12.230 --> 36:14.369
IT IS GONNA BE AWESOME.

36:14.410 --> 36:16.401
WHISPER-SCREAM
AS LOUD AS YOU CAN.

36:16.450 --> 36:17.610
[whispering]
YEAH.

36:17.650 --> 36:20.756
[whispered screams]

36:32.250 --> 36:34.354
- WE'RE--WE'RE JUST SUPPOSED
TO WAIT?

36:34.390 --> 36:39.293
- YEAH. WE'LL JUST WAIT.
IT'S FINE.

36:39.330 --> 36:41.707
- YOU KNOW, MAYBE SOMEONE
SHOULD CHECK ON HER.

36:41.750 --> 36:43.911
- UH, THAT WOULD BE YOU.
- I'M SURE SHE'S FINE.

36:43.960 --> 36:45.404
I DON'T WANT TO SAY
THE WRONG THING AND--

36:45.440 --> 36:48.500
- SARAH, COME ON,
THIS IS RI-GOSH-DAB-DICULOUS.

36:48.550 --> 36:49.574
- OH, NO, NO, NO.
DAD, NO.

36:49.620 --> 36:51.576
- I GOT THIS HANDLED, BABY.

36:51.620 --> 36:53.895
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?
- OH, GOD.

36:53.930 --> 36:55.477
- WELL...

36:55.520 --> 36:57.238
[knock at door]

36:57.280 --> 36:59.965
- AMBER, I'M COMING IN.

37:00.010 --> 37:01.341
OKAY, LET'S GO.

37:01.390 --> 37:04.245
- I DON'T THINK
I CAN DO IT.

37:04.290 --> 37:07.248
I'M SO NERVOUS, AND MY VOICE
IS SOUNDING REALLY BAD.

37:07.290 --> 37:09.008
AND MY FINGERS FEEL HEAW.

37:09.050 --> 37:10.733
I'M SERIOUS.
I'M REALLY NERVOUS.

37:10.780 --> 37:12.919
- AMBER, STOP IT.
STOP IT. STOP IT.

37:12.950 --> 37:16.738
WE ARE GOING.

37:16.780 --> 37:19.431
HONEY...

37:19.470 --> 37:23.474
YOU ARE GONNA BE FANTASTIC.

37:25.310 --> 37:27.619
I MEAN GREAT.

37:37.560 --> 37:39.937
- YOU'RE AN E.V.P.
AT A SOLID COMPANY.

37:39.980 --> 37:43.279
I-I'VE GOT PEOPLE WHO'D KILL
FOR THAT JOB.

37:43.330 --> 37:47.016
- YEAH, UH, LOOK, IT'S JUST
THERE'S A CHANGEOVER GOING ON

37:47.050 --> 37:48.085
AT THE COMPANY,

37:48.120 --> 37:50.600
AND I'M NOT--I'M NOT SURE
IT'S GONNA CONTINUE

37:50.640 --> 37:51.777
TO BE A GOOD FIT.

37:51.820 --> 37:54.050
SO I JUST WANTED TO SEE,
YOU KNOW,

37:54.090 --> 37:55.955
WHAT ELSE IS OUT THERE.

37:55.990 --> 37:57.469
- I MEAN, YOU'VE GOT
A GREAT RESUME,

37:57.510 --> 37:59.751
BUT THERE'S--
THERE'S NOTHING OUT THERE.

37:59.790 --> 38:01.473
I'VE GOT PEOPLE
WITH GOLDEN RESUMES

38:01.520 --> 38:04.478
AND NO JOB TO SEND THEM TO.

38:04.520 --> 38:06.306
THE FACT
THAT YOU HAVE A JOB...

38:06.350 --> 38:08.511
I'D SIT TIGHT.

38:10.420 --> 38:15.767
- WILL YOU CUT YOUR LOSSES
WHEN THERE'S NOTHING TO GAIN

38:15.810 --> 38:20.804
LIKE CHRIST ON THE CROSS
TAKING ALL THE BLAME?

38:20.850 --> 38:24.672
THOUGHT YOU HAD FOREVER,
BUT IT WOUND UP THE SAME

38:24.710 --> 38:29.534
SINGING NOTHIN'
EVER HURT LIKE LOVE

38:29.580 --> 38:31.400
SO YOU GAVE AWAY YOUR BABY

38:31.440 --> 38:32.543
- GLAD YOU MADE IT.
- HEY, SWEETIE.

38:32.580 --> 38:33.922
YEAH, THANKS. JUST A LITTLE
LATE SOMETHING AT WORK.

38:33.960 --> 38:34.927
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
YOU GOOD?

38:34.960 --> 38:36.404
- YEAH. I'M GOOD.
- AWESOME.

38:36.450 --> 38:39.726
- GOOD.
- ...THAT FORTUNE AND FAME

38:39.760 --> 38:41.580
LEFT BEHIND SO_ME SONGS
[cell phone Vibrates]

38:41.620 --> 38:45.932
HEARTACHE AND PAIN
- HMM. WHO'S CHLOE?

38:45.970 --> 38:49.451
- UH, JUST SOMEBODY
FROM STUDENT COUNCIL, NOSY.

38:49.490 --> 38:51.663
- I'M NOT NOSY.
I JUST DON'T KNOW WHO CHLOE IS.

38:51.700 --> 38:54.146
HURRY BACK, OKAY?
THE SHOW'S GONNA START.

38:54.190 --> 38:56.465
- GOD KNOWS YOU'RE TIRED...
- YOU GUYS GOOD?

38:56.500 --> 38:58.809
- YEAH. WE'RE SO GOOD.
SHE'S BEING SO SWEET TO ME.

38:58.850 --> 39:01.637
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.
I MEAN, I'M SORT OF LOVING HER--

39:01.680 --> 39:04.478
- DID I MISS AMBER?
- NO.

39:04.510 --> 39:05.784
- IS SHE COMING ON SOON?
- HONEY, I DON'T--

39:05.820 --> 39:07.788
I DIDN'T BOOK THIS GUY.
I DON'T KNOW.

39:07.820 --> 39:11.824
- CAN'T LET YOUR LIFE'S
LESSONS PASS YOU BY

39:11.860 --> 39:13.851
EH

39:13.900 --> 39:16.619
SO YOU FOUND SOMEONE
WHO'LL MAKE YOU FEEL

39:16.660 --> 39:19.629
ALL FANCY INSIDE...

39:19.660 --> 39:21.173
- HE'S, LIKE, FUNKY,
LIKE, GROOVING.

39:21.220 --> 39:22.619
EVERYBODY'S GROOVING.

39:22.670 --> 39:23.898
SHOULD I BE FUNKY
SO THAT PEOPLE WILL GROOVE?

39:23.940 --> 39:25.180
- NO.
- ARE YOU SURE?

39:25.220 --> 39:26.448
OH, MY GOD. WHAT'S WRONG?
- NOTHING.

39:26.500 --> 39:27.524
- WHAT'S WRONG?
- I FIXED IT.

39:27.570 --> 39:28.707
- OKAY.
- YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.

39:28.740 --> 39:30.014
- GOD, I THINK I'M GONNA
THROW UP.

39:30.050 --> 39:31.665
I FEEL LIKE I'M GONNA THROW UP.
I MIGHT THROW UP.

39:31.710 --> 39:33.018
SHOULD I THROW UP?
- NO. JUST BREATHE.

39:33.060 --> 39:35.085
TAKE A BREATH. TRY.
- OH, MY GOD, I'M STUFFY.

39:35.130 --> 39:36.609
- NO, NO, JUST BREATHE.
- I'M TOO STUFFY.

39:36.650 --> 39:38.606
- NO, BREATHE ALL THE WAY.
[both inhale deeply]

39:38.650 --> 39:40.094
- OH, MY GOD.
I'M SO STUFFY AND NERVOUS.

39:40.130 --> 39:41.165
I'M REALLY NERVOUS.

39:41.200 --> 39:43.543
- I KNOW.

39:43.580 --> 39:45.616
IF I HELPED YOU
THE WAY I HELPED YOUR DAD,

39:45.650 --> 39:46.685
IT WOULD INVOLVE TEQUILA,

39:46.720 --> 39:48.756
SO WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO THINK
OF SOMETHING NEW.

39:48.800 --> 39:51.928
- OH, GOD. OKAY.
[sighs]

39:51.970 --> 39:54.109
- LISTEN...

39:54.150 --> 39:56.869
LOOK AT ME.

39:56.910 --> 39:59.003
YOU KNOW, IF YOU GET NERVOUS,
JUST FORGET THE CROWD

39:59.050 --> 40:00.938
AND FIND ME

40:00.980 --> 40:04.017
AND JUST LOOK AT ME.

40:04.050 --> 40:05.608
- OKAY.
- OKAY?

40:05.640 --> 40:08.108
IT'LL GIVE YOU
SOMETHING TO FOCUS ON.

40:08.160 --> 40:10.048
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

40:10.090 --> 40:12.604
- HEY, DO YOU KNOW WHAT?

40:12.650 --> 40:14.026
- WHAT?

40:14.060 --> 40:17.120
- YOU CAN FLY TOO.

40:17.170 --> 40:18.956
- THANKS.

40:19.000 --> 40:20.581
[cheers and applause]

40:20.620 --> 40:22.759
- HI, MY NAME'S AMBER.

40:22.790 --> 40:24.963
THIS IS A SONG
THAT I'M GONNA SING

40:25.000 --> 40:27.651
THAT'S CALLED
GRAVEYARD SONG.

40:27.700 --> 40:31.557
[cheers and applause]

40:31.600 --> 40:34.660
ALL RIGHT, READY?

40:36.980 --> 40:39.801
[sighs]

40:39.850 --> 40:42.182
[mellow acoustic guitar music]

40:42.230 --> 40:49.159
SMOKE MAKE ME
LOSE MY MEMORIES

40:49.200 --> 40:53.546
DRINK MAKE MY BODY FAIL

40:53.580 --> 40:55.650
- YOU KNOW
WHO SHE REMINDS ME OF?

40:55.690 --> 40:57.999
- JUST HANGING AROUND

40:58.040 --> 41:01.658
- SETH.
- TILL 2:00 OR 3:00

41:01.700 --> 41:07.172
TREATING ME WELL

41:08.880 --> 41:12.839
I'VE BEEN THINKIN'
ABOUT GETTING CLEAN

41:15.050 --> 41:19.703
RISIN' UP AT A DECENT HOUR

41:22.060 --> 41:27.191
WOULD YOU WAKE ME
WHEN YOU LEAVE?

41:27.240 --> 41:31.028
HMM MM MM

41:33.110 --> 41:39.549
IT'S BEEN SO MUCH BETTER
THAN I CAN SAY

41:39.600 --> 41:45.732
IT WILL BE SAD WHEN YOU GO

41:45.770 --> 41:51.743
SINCE THERE IS NOT
AN EASY WAY

41:51.780 --> 41:56.262
I'LL JUST SAY HELLO

41:58.610 --> 42:02.614
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS THE END

42:04.660 --> 42:10.758
THERE ARE ONLY
NEW BEGINNINGS

42:10.800 --> 42:15.760
I'LL BE SEEING YOU AGAIN

42:15.800 --> 42:21.773
HMM MM MM

42:21.810 --> 42:23.801
HMM MM MM
